1
00:00:06,350 --> 00:00:11,150
We were in the final stages of the shoot

2
00:00:11,620 --> 00:00:14,100
for Yumihara Risa's bridal project,

3
00:00:14,280 --> 00:00:15,300
I'll leave this with you.

4
00:00:15,480 --> 00:00:16,480
You got it.

5
00:00:17,410 --> 00:00:19,310
I ended up buying everything Risa uses.

6
00:00:19,638 --> 00:00:21,690
The shades Yumihara-san uses

7
00:00:21,970 --> 00:00:24,000
are incredibly popular at our store.

8
00:00:25,030 --> 00:00:27,046
But an unexpected accident
forced us back to square one.

9
00:00:27,070 --> 00:00:28,639
Everything had to start over.

10
00:00:28,640 --> 00:00:30,550
Here's what you asked for.

11
00:00:30,790 --> 00:00:32,140
Thanks.

12
00:00:32,580 --> 00:00:33,880
I'm about to head out.

13
00:00:33,910 --> 00:00:34,910
I'll leave the rest to you.

14
00:00:34,911 --> 00:00:36,590
Understood. I've got it from here.

15
00:00:37,030 --> 00:00:38,400
Thanks, I appreciate it.

16
00:00:38,870 --> 00:00:40,710
We don't have much
time left before the shoot.

17
00:00:41,230 --> 00:00:42,900
I need to finalize the concept quickly

18
00:00:43,390 --> 00:00:45,090
and get it over to Touma.

19
00:01:42,500 --> 00:01:46,700
"Cosmetic Playlover" Season 2
(Episode 6)

20
00:01:47,530 --> 00:01:50,150
These are the alternative
palettes we discussed.

21
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:52,120
Oh.

22
00:01:52,990 --> 00:01:54,790
Yeah, these are cute.

23
00:01:55,770 --> 00:01:58,190
They'll look different once
they're actually applied,

24
00:01:58,610 --> 00:01:59,769
so I've prepared a few other options...

25
00:01:59,770 --> 00:02:00,770
Great.

26
00:02:01,970 --> 00:02:03,910
I have some overseas exclusives too.

27
00:02:04,330 --> 00:02:06,160
Please, take your pick.

28
00:02:08,220 --> 00:02:09,220
I have to say,

29
00:02:09,590 --> 00:02:12,080
it feels like I'm actually
being pampered. I love it.

30
00:02:14,250 --> 00:02:15,250
Now then...

31
00:02:15,770 --> 00:02:18,580
Let me compare these eyeshadows.

32
00:02:19,990 --> 00:02:20,990
Oof.

33
00:02:26,410 --> 00:02:27,750
Oh, sorry about that.

34
00:02:28,350 --> 00:02:31,140
Um, what's this...?

35
00:02:33,023 --> 00:02:36,553
This is the kind of dress
I'd want to wear personally.

36
00:02:39,180 --> 00:02:40,820
It doesn't really suit my image, does it?

37
00:02:43,210 --> 00:02:44,210
The truth is,

38
00:02:44,620 --> 00:02:46,710
I actually love these cute styles.

39
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:49,750
Things like lace and ruffles...

40
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,470
And I love pretty pinks, too.

41
00:02:52,250 --> 00:02:54,260
I've always been a girly girl at heart.

42
00:02:55,290 --> 00:02:59,960
But it's so different from
the "Yumihara Risa" brand.

43
00:03:00,850 --> 00:03:03,080
So, I only ever wear this stuff in private.

44
00:03:03,950 --> 00:03:05,200
I had no idea.

45
00:03:06,590 --> 00:03:07,590
Actually,

46
00:03:07,670 --> 00:03:09,000
if I could wear my dream dress

47
00:03:09,340 --> 00:03:11,309
for a collaboration with
ROMY, my favorite brand...

48
00:03:11,310 --> 00:03:12,710
it would be like a dream come true.

49
00:03:13,670 --> 00:03:14,670
But,

50
00:03:14,671 --> 00:03:16,010
work is work, after all.

51
00:03:16,810 --> 00:03:18,090
ROMY is your favorite?

52
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:19,800
Yeah.

53
00:03:19,810 --> 00:03:21,839
Even before I started modeling,

54
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:23,930
I was obsessed with ROMY's makeup.

55
00:03:24,080 --> 00:03:26,859
So when I got the offer to be their muse,

56
00:03:26,884 --> 00:03:28,364
I was over the moon.

57
00:03:28,770 --> 00:03:29,770
Oh.

58
00:03:31,990 --> 00:03:33,260
This eyeshadow...

59
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:36,330
It was the first thing I bought
with my part-time job money.

60
00:03:38,420 --> 00:03:39,700
Back when I was a student,

61
00:03:39,940 --> 00:03:42,180
my heart would race just
walking up to the ROMY counter.

62
00:03:42,460 --> 00:03:45,040
Everything was so sparkly and glamorous.

63
00:03:45,100 --> 00:03:46,540
I've been a huge fan ever since.

64
00:03:47,330 --> 00:03:50,000
To do a bridal shoot with ROMY makeup...

65
00:03:50,210 --> 00:03:51,900
I feel so incredibly lucky.

66
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:55,330
And having Touma, my old classmate,
in charge makes it even better.

67
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:08,700
Yumihara-san...

68
00:04:09,590 --> 00:04:11,590
I didn't realize she had
such a history with ROMY.

69
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:15,950
It's true that the dress...

70
00:04:19,540 --> 00:04:22,420
is a total departure from her usual image.

71
00:04:23,130 --> 00:04:25,329
That pink is a bit too soft and feminine.

72
00:04:25,330 --> 00:04:28,050
It doesn't quite fit the
"Yumihara Risa" brand.

73
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:29,840
Thank you, come again.

74
00:04:30,340 --> 00:04:32,339
When it comes to fashion,

75
00:04:32,340 --> 00:04:35,030
everyone has a style that naturally
complements their look and vibe.

76
00:04:36,510 --> 00:04:38,109
Her agency probably knows that,

77
00:04:38,110 --> 00:04:40,350
which is why they're so
careful with her image strategy.

78
00:04:40,620 --> 00:04:42,380
She must understand
that better than anyone.

79
00:04:42,510 --> 00:04:44,230
That's why she hasn't said a word about it.

80
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:51,440
After that,

81
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:54,420
the project reorganization
moved at an incredible pace.

82
00:04:55,760 --> 00:04:57,590
Out of the five bridal shoot concepts,

83
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,720
four have already been finalized.

84
00:05:00,580 --> 00:05:01,580
Now,

85
00:05:01,581 --> 00:05:02,780
only the last one remains.

86
00:05:04,590 --> 00:05:07,960
This combination still feels a bit weak.

87
00:05:08,650 --> 00:05:11,190
The previous concept had such a perfect,

88
00:05:11,360 --> 00:05:13,400
delicate balance that it
really left an impression.

89
00:05:14,280 --> 00:05:17,590
We've already used
the standard bridal look.

90
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:22,590
If we want this to stand out,
we need something with more personality.

91
00:05:34,050 --> 00:05:35,439
By the way, Mamiya-san,

92
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:39,000
you spoke with Yumihara-san at the meeting
the other day, right?

93
00:05:39,610 --> 00:05:40,890
What was your impression of her?

94
00:05:41,970 --> 00:05:43,080
Well...

95
00:05:44,330 --> 00:05:45,620
Let me think.

96
00:05:46,990 --> 00:05:48,810
I've always been a girly girl at heart.

97
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:54,640
But it's so different from
the "Yumihara Risa" brand.

98
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:57,570
So, I only ever wear this stuff in private.

99
00:05:58,630 --> 00:06:00,970
I think she's someone who's
very dedicated to her work,

100
00:06:01,630 --> 00:06:03,086
but also knows how to stay true to herself.

101
00:06:03,110 --> 00:06:05,220
She strikes me as a
person with a very strong will.

102
00:06:06,180 --> 00:06:08,310
A certain kind of... resilience?

103
00:06:10,270 --> 00:06:11,270
Resilience.

104
00:06:13,260 --> 00:06:14,430
I see.

105
00:06:16,150 --> 00:06:19,340
That's a great keyword to bring out
a different side of Yumihara-san.

106
00:06:21,580 --> 00:06:22,580
Maybe we've been

107
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:27,210
too focused on finding the right dress.

108
00:06:29,350 --> 00:06:31,230
In that case, how about a pantsuit?

109
00:06:31,380 --> 00:06:33,400
It would perfectly
showcase her proportions.

110
00:06:33,490 --> 00:06:35,450
- I like it.
- Oh...

111
00:06:35,510 --> 00:06:38,790
It's fresh for a bridal
shoot. It has real impact.

112
00:06:38,990 --> 00:06:40,629
Exactly! Let's go with that!

113
00:06:40,630 --> 00:06:41,680
Wait...

114
00:06:43,020 --> 00:06:44,020
Mamiya-san,

115
00:06:44,570 --> 00:06:45,780
nice assist!

116
00:06:52,880 --> 00:06:53,880
No...

117
00:06:54,220 --> 00:06:55,420
That's not what I meant...

118
00:07:00,543 --> 00:07:02,433
I'm glad we could wrap things up smoothly.

119
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:05,050
- I'll leave it to you all.
- Thank you, everyone.

120
00:07:05,260 --> 00:07:06,390
Good work, everyone.

121
00:07:06,530 --> 00:07:07,530
Good work.

122
00:07:07,770 --> 00:07:08,770
Good work.

123
00:07:08,960 --> 00:07:10,380
I'm looking forward to the results.

124
00:07:11,670 --> 00:07:12,670
- Thank you.
- Good work.

125
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,200
Yoshioka-san,

126
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:17,880
I have a suggestion.

127
00:07:20,880 --> 00:07:24,150
Man... I'm beat.

128
00:07:26,290 --> 00:07:29,370
Is this what it's like
working at headquarters?

129
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:38,310
I've sent the final concept to Touma.

130
00:07:38,993 --> 00:07:40,503
That should be it for now.

131
00:07:44,500 --> 00:07:46,099
(Natsume: The concept is
ready. I just emailed it to you.)

132
00:07:46,100 --> 00:07:48,838
(Touma: Thank you so much. I'll finish the
styling before I head back. Go ahead and sleep.)

133
00:07:51,310 --> 00:07:53,600
Is that guy... really going to be okay?

134
00:08:31,990 --> 00:08:32,990
Natsume-san.

135
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:34,640
I'm home.

136
00:08:35,620 --> 00:08:36,620
You're back.

137
00:08:38,700 --> 00:08:40,520
Yeah, welcome home.

138
00:08:52,380 --> 00:08:53,380
Wait...

139
00:08:53,890 --> 00:08:54,890
He's asleep?!

140
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:58,480
Is he really out?

141
00:08:59,860 --> 00:09:00,860
There we go.

142
00:09:06,510 --> 00:09:07,510
Are you okay?

143
00:09:09,830 --> 00:09:11,030
You woke me up... sorry...

144
00:09:12,140 --> 00:09:13,510
Natsume-san, come sleep too...

145
00:09:18,890 --> 00:09:22,060
I heard you've been
working really hard lately.

146
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:25,000
I'm proud of you.

147
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:26,480
You're doing a great job.

148
00:09:28,740 --> 00:09:30,270
Did Nanjo-san tell you that?

149
00:09:31,950 --> 00:09:33,250
Why would he say that...

150
00:09:34,950 --> 00:09:37,120
Working hard is just
what I'm supposed to do...

151
00:09:38,010 --> 00:09:39,010
Huh?

152
00:09:43,020 --> 00:09:44,860
I'm going to learn everything I can.

153
00:09:46,410 --> 00:09:48,080
I'll do it in two years,

154
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:52,880
and then I'll come back to you.

155
00:10:23,910 --> 00:10:24,910
Morning.

156
00:10:25,250 --> 00:10:26,250
Morning.

157
00:10:30,380 --> 00:10:31,380
You okay?

158
00:10:31,780 --> 00:10:33,800
You were out like a light last night.

159
00:10:35,310 --> 00:10:38,410
A quick hug from you is all
I need to recharge. I'm fine.

160
00:10:39,950 --> 00:10:41,670
Don't you think "all I need" is a bit much?

161
00:10:44,740 --> 00:10:45,980
Here, these are the test shots.

162
00:10:46,660 --> 00:10:47,660
Oh.

163
00:10:49,100 --> 00:10:50,580
You finished the last set too?

164
00:10:51,630 --> 00:10:53,150
The files have already been sent over.

165
00:10:53,550 --> 00:10:54,680
That's impressive.

166
00:10:56,510 --> 00:10:57,510
Good work.

167
00:10:57,900 --> 00:10:58,900
Seriously, thanks.

168
00:11:00,010 --> 00:11:01,980
I'll make sure these get delivered.

169
00:11:02,790 --> 00:11:03,880
I'll leave it to you then.

170
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:05,200
Yeah.

171
00:11:08,430 --> 00:11:10,000
Touma went to Osaka on a business trip.

172
00:11:10,850 --> 00:11:11,240
So cute.

173
00:11:11,241 --> 00:11:12,480
While I was at headquarters,

174
00:11:12,980 --> 00:11:15,460
finishing the final checks with the staff.

175
00:11:16,030 --> 00:11:17,350
Then, I headed back to the store.

176
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:21,040
Mamiya-san.

177
00:11:21,140 --> 00:11:21,990
Yeah?

178
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:24,150
Today, while you were at headquarters,

179
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:26,810
a male student came in wanting to try
the men's skincare line.

180
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:28,379
I was the one who helped him.

181
00:11:28,380 --> 00:11:29,230
I see.

182
00:11:29,370 --> 00:11:31,329
He said he came in
because he saw your poster.

183
00:11:31,330 --> 00:11:32,290
Wait, mine?

184
00:11:32,330 --> 00:11:33,330
Yes.

185
00:11:33,420 --> 00:11:35,189
He said he was nervous
since it was his first time,

186
00:11:35,190 --> 00:11:37,060
but he worked up the courage to walk in.

187
00:11:37,670 --> 00:11:40,000
I really felt for him.

188
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:44,610
Being part of someone's
"first time" like that...

189
00:11:44,690 --> 00:11:46,690
It just made me really happy.

190
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:50,220
Helping customers is so rewarding.

191
00:11:51,870 --> 00:11:53,089
Anyway, I'll get back to work.

192
00:11:53,090 --> 00:11:54,090
Okay.

193
00:11:56,830 --> 00:11:57,490
She's right.
Welcome.

194
00:11:58,231 --> 00:11:59,370
As Beauty Advisors,

195
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:03,170
we're part of so many
milestones in our customers' lives.

196
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:08,470
Someone buying a
lipstick as a gift for a friend.

197
00:12:09,560 --> 00:12:13,440
Someone buying sunscreen for a trip abroad.

198
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:17,880
Or someone asking for
makeup advice for a job interview.

199
00:12:20,330 --> 00:12:21,330
And then,

200
00:12:24,450 --> 00:12:29,740
there are those who cherish an eyeshadow
bought with their very first paycheck.

201
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:32,320
Yumihara-san

202
00:12:33,070 --> 00:12:34,700
isn't just the muse for ROMY,

203
00:12:35,730 --> 00:12:37,050
she's also a valued customer.

204
00:12:39,733 --> 00:12:41,193
Tomorrow's shoot

205
00:12:41,770 --> 00:12:43,500
has to be a success.

206
00:12:53,790 --> 00:12:54,790
Hello?

207
00:12:55,510 --> 00:12:56,510
Good work today.

208
00:12:58,070 --> 00:12:59,800
Oh, I'm just about to leave the store.

209
00:13:01,970 --> 00:13:03,560
Let's grab dinner before we head home.

210
00:13:04,370 --> 00:13:05,370
Sure.

211
00:13:13,540 --> 00:13:15,049
After dealing with all that trouble,

212
00:13:15,050 --> 00:13:16,570
that drink tasted amazing.

213
00:13:16,700 --> 00:13:17,869
Oh, but since the shoot is tomorrow,

214
00:13:17,870 --> 00:13:19,429
I stuck to just one.

215
00:13:19,430 --> 00:13:20,430
Right.

216
00:13:21,550 --> 00:13:23,870
I feel like I'm finally getting
a taste of the real world.

217
00:13:24,730 --> 00:13:26,870
Interacting with people
from other companies...

218
00:13:27,490 --> 00:13:29,280
Just to pull off one project,

219
00:13:29,530 --> 00:13:31,850
so many people with different
roles have to work together.

220
00:13:32,030 --> 00:13:33,180
I see.

221
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:36,299
In terms of broadening my horizons,

222
00:13:36,300 --> 00:13:37,750
it's been a great experience.

223
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:41,120
But right now, I just
want the shoot to go well

224
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:43,610
so I can get back to focusing on the store.

225
00:13:44,140 --> 00:13:45,140
Yeah.

226
00:13:48,410 --> 00:13:49,410
Huh?

227
00:13:50,060 --> 00:13:53,350
What's with the one-word answers?

228
00:13:54,603 --> 00:13:55,953
Are you drunk already?

229
00:14:02,020 --> 00:14:04,060
We're home~

230
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:12,400
Hey.

231
00:14:12,950 --> 00:14:13,980
Natsume-san.

232
00:14:16,340 --> 00:14:17,340
Touma.

233
00:14:17,860 --> 00:14:18,860
Take it easy.

234
00:14:20,060 --> 00:14:21,080
Natsume-san.

235
00:14:22,620 --> 00:14:24,470
I worked really hard on that trip.

236
00:14:26,560 --> 00:14:27,560
I know.

237
00:14:27,650 --> 00:14:29,700
I worked really hard on the styling, too.

238
00:14:31,560 --> 00:14:33,000
Yes, you did.

239
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:36,000
I wanted to see you so badly,

240
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:38,370
so I rushed back as fast as I could.

241
00:14:40,470 --> 00:14:41,470
I see.

242
00:14:47,180 --> 00:14:49,350
I want you to praise me...

243
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:52,640
Is that okay?

244
00:14:52,990 --> 00:14:53,990
Oh.

245
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:58,940
Exhaustion plus alcohol...

246
00:14:59,730 --> 00:15:01,850
Touma is definitely not himself.

247
00:15:06,560 --> 00:15:08,590
Please praise me...

248
00:15:09,393 --> 00:15:10,393
Please...

249
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:16,520
You did great.

250
00:15:18,070 --> 00:15:19,070
Good boy.

251
00:15:19,450 --> 00:15:20,450
More.

252
00:15:21,310 --> 00:15:22,590
Tell me more.

253
00:15:24,630 --> 00:15:26,430
You work so hard, it's amazing.

254
00:15:28,380 --> 00:15:29,500
And you're so handsome.

255
00:15:30,170 --> 00:15:31,570
You're so talented with your hands.

256
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:33,930
And you smell so good.

257
00:15:40,690 --> 00:15:42,580
I love you so much, Natsume-san.

258
00:15:43,440 --> 00:15:44,540
What about you?

259
00:15:46,590 --> 00:15:47,690
I love you too.

260
00:15:47,900 --> 00:15:49,000
What do you love about me?

261
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,310
You're reliable.

262
00:15:54,580 --> 00:15:55,750
And hardworking.

263
00:15:56,980 --> 00:15:58,080
And you're so kind.

264
00:16:02,530 --> 00:16:04,600
I love you the most, Natsume-san.

265
00:16:05,710 --> 00:16:06,710
Hey.

266
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:08,320
Hey, wait a second...

267
00:16:15,060 --> 00:16:17,720
I was so lonely while we were apart.

268
00:16:22,070 --> 00:16:23,950
Don't just say things
like that out of nowhere.

269
00:16:47,990 --> 00:16:50,850
I had no idea you were such a clingy drunk.

270
00:16:52,620 --> 00:16:54,660
It's the first time I've
seen it. You surprised me.

271
00:16:55,790 --> 00:16:57,090
Are you feeling better now?

272
00:16:58,490 --> 00:16:59,490
Yeah.

273
00:17:00,280 --> 00:17:02,080
It's the first time I've
ever been like that.

274
00:17:04,090 --> 00:17:05,090
Really?

275
00:17:06,140 --> 00:17:07,319
I only had one drink.

276
00:17:07,320 --> 00:17:08,670
I even surprised myself.

277
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:15,700
Listen.

278
00:17:17,560 --> 00:17:18,960
Don't push yourself too hard.

279
00:17:23,020 --> 00:17:27,250
If you get sick while you're in Paris,

280
00:17:29,010 --> 00:17:30,810
I won't be able to just
rush over to see you.

281
00:17:33,620 --> 00:17:35,620
No matter how exhausted
you are when you get home,

282
00:17:36,730 --> 00:17:38,370
I won't be there to tuck you into bed.

283
00:17:40,990 --> 00:17:42,750
And if you get drunk
like you did yesterday,

284
00:17:43,740 --> 00:17:45,180
I won't be there for you to lean on.

285
00:17:48,640 --> 00:17:49,800
Once we're long-distance,

286
00:17:51,030 --> 00:17:52,030
no matter what happens,

287
00:17:53,220 --> 00:17:54,220
I'll...

288
00:17:57,240 --> 00:17:59,440
only be able to worry from afar.

289
00:18:12,820 --> 00:18:14,260
So you have to promise me

290
00:18:17,170 --> 00:18:18,370
that you won't overdo it.

291
00:18:22,120 --> 00:18:23,120
I promise.

292
00:18:27,480 --> 00:18:28,580
You seem really anxious.

293
00:18:30,250 --> 00:18:31,730
After seeing you like that yesterday,

294
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:33,000
how could I not be?

295
00:18:43,980 --> 00:18:44,980
I'm sorry.

296
00:18:48,620 --> 00:18:49,620
It's okay.

297
00:19:14,700 --> 00:19:15,919
Should we scatter some rose petals?

298
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:17,460
- No, I don't think we need that.
- Oh?

299
00:19:18,210 --> 00:19:20,490
They're already prepared,
so let's just leave it for now.

300
00:19:26,750 --> 00:19:28,390
Sahashi, do you need any help?

301
00:19:28,880 --> 00:19:29,880
I'm good for now.

302
00:19:30,080 --> 00:19:32,170
Could you assist me
when I start the makeup?

303
00:19:32,640 --> 00:19:33,640
You got it.

304
00:19:34,390 --> 00:19:35,300
What do you mean?

305
00:19:35,301 --> 00:19:38,469
- There's a traffic jam due to an accident...
- A jam? What am I supposed to do about that?

306
00:19:38,470 --> 00:19:39,420
I'm so sorry.

307
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:41,000
Someone will have to go pick them up...

308
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:44,489
This is the absolute worst.

309
00:19:44,490 --> 00:19:47,260
Um... is something wrong?

310
00:19:47,340 --> 00:19:48,890
The roses we ordered

311
00:19:49,020 --> 00:19:51,430
are stuck in traffic
because of an accident.

312
00:19:52,260 --> 00:19:53,490
Someone needs to go get them.

313
00:19:54,370 --> 00:19:56,350
I'll go.

314
00:19:56,550 --> 00:19:58,200
Wait, but...

315
00:19:58,580 --> 00:20:00,840
I'm mostly just here to observe anyway.

316
00:20:01,450 --> 00:20:03,036
I'm the only one with free time right now.

317
00:20:03,060 --> 00:20:04,960
The rest of you should keep getting ready.

318
00:20:06,100 --> 00:20:07,100
Understood.

319
00:20:07,650 --> 00:20:09,650
- Thanks, I appreciate it.
- We're counting on you.

320
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:12,290
Yumihara Risa-san will be arriving shortly.

321
00:20:12,850 --> 00:20:14,060
I'm heading out then.

322
00:20:14,180 --> 00:20:15,180
Good luck.

323
00:20:17,340 --> 00:20:18,340
Natsume-san.

324
00:20:18,970 --> 00:20:20,170
Oh, sorry.

325
00:20:20,240 --> 00:20:21,240
About assisting you...

326
00:20:23,470 --> 00:20:24,470
Be careful out there.

327
00:20:26,510 --> 00:20:28,150
Thanks, I'm off.

328
00:20:31,477 --> 00:20:33,907
Will Mamiya-san be okay on his own?

329
00:20:34,290 --> 00:20:35,420
He'll be fine.

330
00:20:36,260 --> 00:20:38,010
Let's just focus on our own jobs.

331
00:20:38,820 --> 00:20:39,820
Right.

332
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:01,230
Natsume-san,

333
00:21:02,120 --> 00:21:04,050
you really never change, do you?

334
00:21:05,700 --> 00:21:07,120
Always putting yourself second,

335
00:21:07,920 --> 00:21:09,540
always thinking of others.

336
00:21:12,940 --> 00:21:13,940
Hey.

337
00:21:14,600 --> 00:21:18,010
Touma, do you have a lover?

338
00:21:18,790 --> 00:21:19,790
What makes you say that?

339
00:21:20,950 --> 00:21:21,950
Woman's intuition.

340
00:21:22,460 --> 00:21:23,480
I don't know,

341
00:21:24,170 --> 00:21:26,230
your expression is much
softer than it used to be.

342
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:30,020
You must be very happy together.

343
00:21:30,580 --> 00:21:31,580
Well...

344
00:21:33,060 --> 00:21:34,060
What are they like?

345
00:21:34,820 --> 00:21:36,490
What do you love about them?

346
00:21:43,340 --> 00:21:44,340
Everything.

347
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:49,200
Their kindness...

348
00:21:50,280 --> 00:21:51,640
The way they try to act tough...

349
00:21:53,030 --> 00:21:54,130
When they're happy,

350
00:21:55,160 --> 00:21:56,260
when they're anxious...

351
00:21:57,900 --> 00:21:59,940
Even the way their expressions
are always changing.

352
00:22:01,720 --> 00:22:03,940
I'm head over heels for every part of them.

353
00:22:08,530 --> 00:22:09,860
They have this inner warmth

354
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:13,170
that just naturally saves
everyone around them.

355
00:22:21,440 --> 00:22:22,790
Sorry to keep you waiting.

356
00:22:23,160 --> 00:22:24,340
Thank you.

357
00:22:39,010 --> 00:22:40,010
Here you go.

358
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:45,440
Thanks.

359
00:22:47,170 --> 00:22:48,170
Um...

360
00:22:51,180 --> 00:22:52,480
This outfit...

361
00:22:53,320 --> 00:22:56,740
I heard it was your idea, Mamiya-san.

362
00:23:01,250 --> 00:23:02,250
For all these years,

363
00:23:02,660 --> 00:23:05,070
thank you so much for loving ROMY.

364
00:23:07,770 --> 00:23:09,160
As a ROMY Beauty Advisor,

365
00:23:10,040 --> 00:23:11,910
please allow me to
offer you my best wishes.

366
00:23:15,780 --> 00:23:17,050
Mamiya-san.

367
00:23:23,660 --> 00:23:24,676
I'll leave the rest to you.

368
00:23:24,700 --> 00:23:25,700
Of course.

369
00:23:29,240 --> 00:23:30,490
Alright, let's start the shoot.

370
00:23:31,060 --> 00:23:32,060
Here we go.

371
00:23:34,090 --> 00:23:35,120
One more.

372
00:23:36,430 --> 00:23:37,430
Yeah.

373
00:23:39,680 --> 00:23:42,040
I didn't realize Yumihara-san
could pull off this look too.

374
00:23:42,280 --> 00:23:43,489
She's so cute.

375
00:23:43,490 --> 00:23:46,650
It's a whole new side of her.

376
00:23:49,090 --> 00:23:50,669
Yeah, that's great.

377
00:23:50,670 --> 00:23:52,760
Oh, this is good.

378
00:23:58,360 --> 00:24:00,869
Next up is the ring shot.
Everyone, get ready.

379
00:24:00,870 --> 00:24:02,670
Please.

380
00:24:03,190 --> 00:24:04,190
Taking the shot.

381
00:24:05,090 --> 00:24:06,090
Nice.

382
00:24:07,090 --> 00:24:08,090
Perfect.

383
00:24:20,850 --> 00:24:21,850
No matter what,

384
00:24:23,050 --> 00:24:24,910
I want to protect this sincere person.

385
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:27,160
This one is great.

386
00:24:38,980 --> 00:24:39,980
Natsume-san.

387
00:24:46,120 --> 00:24:47,826
(Next Episode)
Where are you going with Mamiya-kun?

388
00:24:47,850 --> 00:24:48,850
Must be nice.

389
00:24:49,130 --> 00:24:50,920
You're like a little kid.

390
00:24:51,040 --> 00:24:52,706
I don't know when
we'll get to do this again.

391
00:24:52,730 --> 00:24:57,130
There are only six months
left before Touma leaves Japan.
